{
  "_comment": "Shared detection taxonomy for Canary. Maps every detector type to a sensitivity class, regulatory tags, and a standalone risk weight (1=negligible, 10=catastrophic single-value compromise). Per-hit risk score = risk_weight * confidence_multiplier. Consumed by dashboard.py, wrapped.py, bin/canary-stats, bin/canary-card, bin/canary-badge — read it, never hardcode weights elsewhere. Regulatory tags marked with a trailing * on US-only identifiers mean 'equivalent regime', not literal EU jurisdiction; surface that nuance in UI copy. Weights are researched, not arbitrary: aws_access_key/aba_routing/npi_number are deliberately LOW because an access-key-id, a routing number on every check, and a public NPPES directory id are not secret standing alone.",
  "confidence_multiplier": { "high": 1.0, "medium": 0.6, "low": 0.3, "certain": 1.0 },
  "_scoring": "Weighted risk score S = sum over all hits of (risk_weight * confidence_multiplier). Letter grade = the first grade_bands entry whose max >= S (scan top to bottom), except A+ requires S==0 exactly; if S exceeds every band's max the grade is the fallback 'F'. Every scoring surface (dashboard, wrapped, stats, card, badge) MUST implement this identically so the grade never disagrees across tools.",
  "grade_bands": [
    { "grade": "A+", "max": 0 },
    { "grade": "A",  "max": 8 },
    { "grade": "B",  "max": 25 },
    { "grade": "C",  "max": 75 },
    { "grade": "D",  "max": 250 }
  ],
  "grade_fallback": "F",
  "_personas": "Compute context = {total, distinct_types, dominant_class (sensitivity_class with the highest summed hit count), dominant_family (family with the highest hit count), night (>=30% of hits have local hour in 00:00-04:59), tripped (any canary_tripped hit)}. Walk personas top to bottom and return the first whose cond matches: 'clean' -> total==0; 'tripped' -> tripped; 'class:X' -> dominant_class==X; 'night' -> night true; 'polyglot' -> distinct_types>=12; 'oversharer' -> total>=100; 'family:X' -> dominant_family==X; 'default' -> always. dashboard.py and wrapped.py MUST use this same table+algorithm so the persona agrees.",
  "personas": [
    { "cond": "clean",            "label": "The Untouchable",     "emoji": "🕊️", "blurb": "Nothing leaked. The canary sings." },
